ated everything into one package. it should be supported. Let me verify the MSTest v3 compatibility requirements — it supports .NET Framework 4.6.2 and above, .NET 6+, and .NET Standard 2.0, so net462 is compatible. The actual changes are straightforward: swap out the package references in the .csproj file, but the test code itself remains unchanged since the namespace and attributes are still the same in v3.","outputTokens":1038,"requestId":"7033:1BB519:389CF4:41FE75:69F2BD82"},"id":"69c3841e-a191-49b5-bace-cbce4163dba6","timestamp":"2026-04-30T02:25:25.671Z","parentId":"bb1902c1-eab0-4fb7-82a9-951aa97812e3"}
